--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  The Disciplined Disciple Compiler          
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  0) You will need working copies of GHC (at least 6.8.1) and GCC installed.

  1) Make a local copy of the build file.

     $ cp make/build.mk.sample make/build.mk
    
  2) Build the compiler, runtime system and external libraries.
  
     $ make
     
  3) Build the libraries and run the test code (with optimisations enabled)
  
     $ bin/war -ddc O
     
  4) Copy the compiler binary to your ~/bin dir 
      (where ~/bin is in your PATH)
  
     $ cp bin/ddc ~/bin

  5) Create an alias to give ddc the path to its libraries and runtime.
      (You'll probably want to add this to your .profile, or similar)
  
     $ alias ddc='ddc -basedir $(DDC_BUILD)'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    see doc/HACKING for more info or go to http://code.google.com/p/disciple
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
     
